    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In botany, a stamen is the male or fertilizing organ of a flowering plant, consisting of two parts, the anther, which is a double-celled sac containing the pollen, and the filament, a slender footstalk supporting the anther.</Note_Text>
